# imgtool Argument Parser

## Build

g++ main.cpp Args.cpp -o imgtool

## Usage

./imgtool <input_image> <output_image> [options]

## Supported Options

Flags:
--grayscale  (-g)
--blur       (-l)
--flipH      (-h)
--flipV      (-v)

Options with values:
--brighten N (-b N)  where N in [-255,255]
--rotate N   (-r N)  where N in {0,90,180,270}

Also supports:

--brighten=20
--rotate=90

## Examples

Valid:

./imgtool in.png out.png --grayscale

./imgtool in.png out.png -g -b 20 --rotate=90

./imgtool "my image.png" out.png --blur

Invalid:

./imgtool in.png
Error: missing output file

./imgtool in.png out.png --brighten
Error: --brighten requires an integer value

./imgtool in.png out.png --brighten twenty
Error: invalid integer for --brighten: twenty